Chemometric Model Sample Selection

JH

6/10/2015

Way back in 2010/2011 a set of samples were selected to serve as the basis for a chemometric model that predicts chemical composition from NIR camera imagery. Sample selection was based on NIR imagery and an existing chemo model of Roger Meders. At that time I produced a plot showing the variation in predicted composition at pixel level and averaged over 20 mm (approximately the intended sample size). Overlaid on this plot were the selected samples.

Initially 59 samples were selected. Later (Jan 2011) a further 50 samples were selected and sent to UBC for analysis.

Armin would like a publication quality version of this plot.

Original analysis in matlab. See ChemMapping/ChemSampleSelection1/*

X = read.csv('/home/harrinjj/Desktop/Dropbox/sample_selection.csv',na.strings='NaN',header=F)

isel1 = X$sel1==1
isel2 = X$sel2==1
XX = data.frame(Glc=c(X$Glc,X$Glc.avg,X$Glc.avg[isel1],X$Glc.avg[isel2]),
                Gal=c(X$Gal,X$Gal.avg,X$Gal.avg[isel1],X$Gal.avg[isel2]),
                Lig=c(X$Lig,X$Lig.avg,X$Lig.avg[isel1],X$Lig.avg[isel2]),
                set=c(rep('raw',nrow(X)),
                      rep('avg',nrow(X)),
                      rep('sel1',sum(isel1)),
                      rep('sel2',sum(isel2)))
                )
XX$set = factor(XX$set, levels=c('raw','avg','sel1','sel2'), ordered=T)
library(lattice)
library(gridExtra)
## Loading required package: grid
myplot = function(...) {
  xyplot(..., pch=c(1,1,1,1), cex=c(0.3,0.3,1,1), col=c('blue','cadetblue1','red','black'),
         panel = function(...) {
           panel.grid(h=-1, v=-1)
           panel.xyplot(...)
         })
}
grid.arrange(
  myplot(Glc ~ Lig, group=set, XX, xlim=c(15,45), ylim=c(35,60)),
  myplot(Gal ~ Lig, group=set, XX, xlim=c(15,45), ylim=c(0,12)),
  myplot(Gal ~ Glc, group=set, XX, xlim=c(35,60), ylim=c(0,12)),
  nrow=1
  )

Perhaps the point clouds would work better as overlaid transparent 2D histograms?

library(ggplot2)
myplot2 = function(xvar,yvar,xlim,ylim) {
  ggplot(data=XX, aes_string(xvar,yvar)) + 
    stat_binhex(data=XX[XX$set=='raw',], aes(fill='red',  alpha=..count..), bins=100, na.rm=TRUE) + 
    stat_binhex(data=XX[XX$set=='avg',], aes(fill='blue', alpha=..count..), bins=100, na.rm=TRUE) + 
        guides(fill=FALSE, alpha=FALSE, col=FALSE) + 
    geom_point(data=XX[XX$set=='sel1'|XX$set=='sel2',], aes(col=set), na.rm=TRUE) + 
    coord_cartesian(xlim=xlim, ylim=ylim) +
    scale_colour_manual(values=c('red','black')) +
    theme_bw()
  }
grid.arrange(
  myplot2(yvar='Glc',xvar='Lig', xlim=c(15,45), ylim=c(35,60)),
  myplot2(yvar='Gal',xvar='Lig', xlim=c(15,45), ylim=c(0,12)),
  myplot2(yvar='Gal',xvar='Glc', xlim=c(35,60), ylim=c(0,12)),
  nrow=1
  )
